  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 160&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Score the fatty side of the <strong>pork belly</strong>&nbsp;in a criss-cross pattern, deep enough to reach the meat below, then rub the fatty side with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat &amp; once very hot, add the<strong>&nbsp;pork belly</strong>, fat-side down &amp; cook for 3-5 min or until nicely coloured</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1199.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1199.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1199.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1199.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1199.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, zest the <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> onto a plate</p>\r\n<p>Combine the<strong> ground cumin</strong>, <strong>allspice</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with the<strong> orange zest&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>pork belly</strong> <strong>fat</strong> is nicely browned, leave it to cool slightly</p>\r\n<p>Once cool enough to handle, add the <strong>pork belly</strong> to the plate and rub it with the <strong>spices&nbsp;</strong>until evenly coated&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
